4300.name: Operation Document - 2/10
4300.description: This document was found in the cargo of the Trade Guild. The document contains various information regarding Innadril. How could this have happened...?

4309.name: Completed Operation Order
4309.description: A book consisting of 10 pages of operation orders bound together. Who should we take it to...?

4310.name: Iason Heine's Bill
4310.description: The bill's face value is 1,000 adena. If you take it to Roman of the Blacksmith Guild in Innadril, you can use it to purchase various ingredients.

4311.name: Gillian's Diary
4311.description: Gillian's diary. The last entry was made one year ago.

4312.name: Gillian's Notes
4312.description: Partial lyrics of a song Gillian was jotting down.

4313.name: Unfinished Music
4313.description: An unfinished music score of a song that Gilian composed for a former lover.

4314.name: Gillian's Heart
4314.description: The heart that Gillian threw out to forget his feelings of love. Return it to the Revenant of Gillian.

4315.name: Gandi Tribe's Relic
4315.description: The sacred object of the Gandi Tribe that has been recovered from Bugbears. Take it to Gandi Chief Chianta in the Town of Dion.

4316.name: Swan's Flute
4316.description: A flute that Troubadour Swan had obtained as a gift for Musician Nanarin.

4317.name: Swan's Letter
4317.description: A love letter that Troubadour Swan wants to send to Musician Nanarin along with the flute. Take them to Musician Nanarin.

4318.name: Event Clothes
4318.description: A gift that Musician Nanarin is sending to Musician Barbado. Take it to Barbado.

4319.name: Nanarin's Flute
4319.description: A gift that Musician Nanarin is sending to Musician Barbado. Take it to Barbado.

4320.name: Sabrin's Black Beer
4320.description: A gift that Musician Nanarin is sending to Musician Barbado. Take it to Barbado.

4321.name: Stolen Black Beer
4321.description: Black beer that was stolen from Jonas. Take it to Trader Sabrin.

4322.name: Stolen Event Clothes
4322.description: Event clothes that were stolen from Trader Sonia. Take them to Guard Xaber.

4323.name: Clothes Chest Key
4323.description: The key given by Bard Swan. Use this key to open the clothes chest and retrieve the event clothes.

4324.name: Beer Chest Key
4324.description: The key given by Bard Swan. Use this key to open the beer chest and get the black beer out of it.

4325.name: Fairy Leaf
4325.description: A leaf given by Fairy Mimyu to put on the fairy's neck wound that was inflicted by a Hatchling.

4326.name: Ratman Scavenger's Skull
4326.description: Heads of Ratman Scavengers that you hunted after receiving a request from Katari. Collect 10 of them and take them to Katari.

4327.name: Turek War Hound's Tail
4327.description: The tails of Turek war Hounds that Piotur asks you to catch. Collect 10 of them and take them to Piotur.

4328.name: Tyrant Kingpin's Heart
4328.description: Tyrant Kingpin's Heart. Take it to Elder Casian.

4329.name: Trisalim Tarantula's Venom Sac
4329.description: The venom sacs of Trisalim Tarantulas that Magister Joan asked you to hunt. Collect three and take them to Magister Joan.

4330.name: Penitent's Manacles
4330.description: A heavy set of manacles forged at the Black Judge's behest. Take them to the Black Judge.

4331.name: Manual of Manacles
4331.description: Blacksmith's Frame x 1, Steel x 5, Adamantite Nugget x 2, Silver Nugget x 10, Cokes x 10

4332.name: Tarlk Amulet
4332.description: A mark that can be obtained by catching a Tarlk Bugbear or a Tarlk Basilisk. Collect 30 and take them to a Clan Hall Herald.

4333.name: Contest Certificate
4333.description: A certificate that one can present to participate in the hunt for Tarlk Basilisks, a preliminary contest for a Clan Hall Siege War.

4334.name: Ant's Ichor
4334.description: Bodily fluids extracted from ants or ant captains. Collect 20 and take them to Elder Casian.

4335.name: Noble Ant's Nerve Tissue
4335.description: The nerve tissue harvested from a Noble Ant's head. Take it to Elder Casian along with the Ant's Ichor.

4336.name: Casian's Enzyme
4336.description: Enzyme created by Elder Casian. Find the Ant Larvae sleeping within the Ant Nest Dungeon and administer the enzyme to them.

4337.name: Alligator Leather
4337.description: Pelts obtained from alligators caught on Alligator Island. You can sell it to Enverun.

4338.name: Blue Back Alligator Leather
4338.description: Leather from Blue Back Alligators caught on Alligator Island. You can sell it to Enverun at a high price.

4339.name: Jewel Studded Alligator Leather
4339.description: A piece of Jewel Studded Alligator Leather caught on Alligator Island. You can sell it to Enverun at a high price.

4340.name: Certificate of Approval to Create a Belt
4340.description: If you take a sufficient amount of Alligator Leather and show it to Gabana, a master leather craftsman, you can have an Alligator Leather Belt made.

4341.name: Certificate of Approval to Create a Purse
4341.description: If you take a sufficient amount of Alligator Leather and show it to Gabana, a master leather craftsman, you can have an Alligator Leather Purse made.

4342.name: Water Crystal
4342.description: A lump of crystal that contains the energy of water. You should find the Stone Statue of Water and dedicate it to the statue.

4343.name: Fire Crystal
4343.description: A lump of crystal that contains the energy of fire. You should find the Stone Statue of Fire and dedicate it to the statue.

4344.name: Wind Crystal
4344.description: A lump of crystal that contains the energy of wind. You should find the Stone Statue of Wind and dedicate it to the statue.

4345.name: Earth Crystal
4345.description: A lump of crystal that contains the energy of earth. You should find the Stone Statue of Earth and dedicate it to the statue.

4346.name: Dark Crystal
4346.description: A lump of crystal that contains the energy of darkness. You should find the Stone Statue of Darkness and dedicate it to the statue.

4347.name: Crystal of Light
4347.description: A lump of crystal that contains the energy of light. You should find the Stone Statue of Light and dedicate it to the statue.

4348.name: Jade Crystal
4348.description: Jade crystals that had been gathered from the Enchanted Valley. Collect them and take them to Bentley of Hunters Village.

4349.name: Bust of Ancient Goddess
4349.description: A statue of a goddess that was created by the ancient sculptor Berona in ancient times.

4350.name: The Work of the ancient sculptor Berona
4350.description: A statue created by the ancient sculptor Berona. It has not been evaluated by antique experts yet.

4351.name: Ancient Statue of Goddess: Prototype
4351.description: A statue created by Berona, an ancient sculptor. - Prototype

4352.name: Ancient Statue of Goddess: Original
4352.description: A statue created by Berona, a sculptor in ancient times. - Original

4353.name: Ancient Statue of Goddess: Replica
4353.description: Replicated statues that have been created by present day sculptors who imitated Berona's works.

4354.name: Ancient Statue of Goddess: Forgery
4354.description: Forgeries that have been created in imitation of the ancient sculptor Berona's works.

4359.name: Barrel of Liquor
4359.description: A barrel that is filled to the brim with delicious and fragrant liquor. The barrel is very heavy.

4360.name: Precious Scarab
4360.description: A scarab that is transparent and shines like a precious stone. Among hustlers it is traded at a high price.

4361.name: Simbelmyne
4361.description: A type of flower that is believed to have the power to heal sickness. It is a favorite of elves.

4362.name: Odd (looking) Doll
4362.description: It is a strange looking statue of a living creature that looks like an imp. It is an orc's favorite item.

4363.name: Scarlet Dress
4363.description: A very attractive scarlet Aden-style dress designed for a virtuous lady.

4364.name: Nebulite Orb
4364.description: It is made by cutting Nebulite into a spherical shape. Take this to Magic Trader Cema in Hardin's Academy.

4365.name: Ectoplasm Liqueur
4365.description: An exotic tasting liqueur made from ectoplasm. Very popular among connoisseurs.

4366.name: Prince's Trophy
4366.description: The winning trophy that Prince Malcom won in a dance competition. You can sell it at a store or keep it as a souvenir.

4367.name: Prince's Autobiography
4367.description: The autobiography of Prince Malcom that bears his hand-written signature. Sell it at a store.

4368.name: Prince's Bust
4368.description: A statue of Prince Malcom made of pure gold. Although quite ugly, it will fetch a handsome price.

4369.name: Silk Handkerchief
4369.description: A beautiful and elaborate handkerchief decorated with a flower pattern and lace. Its design could attract the attention of princes and princesses.

4370.name: Luxurious Goblet
4370.description: A luxuriously designed goblet. It seems to be an object made during the period of the Elmo Aden Empire.

4371.name: Scepter of Darkness
4371.description: A staff that gives off dark M. Atk. On its handle, the words "Great Demon King" are engraved.

4372.name: Succubus Perfume
4372.description: Perfume used by Succubus noblewomen. A very strong fragrance, not popular among Elves and Humans.

4373.name: Succubus Mirror
4373.description: A mirror used by Succubus noblewomen when they put on cosmetics. It is also said to be used occasionally by blood queens.

4374.name: Heart of Darkness
4374.description: A heart-shaped stone piece that gives off the aura of dark M. Atk. On its reverse, the words "I love you Merkenis!" are engraved.

4375.name: Royal Orc Totem
4375.description: A totem made by carving out a whole lump of red granite.

4376.name: Pearl Trodden/Trampled By A Wild Hog
4376.description: A walnut sized bead that is smeared with dirt. Perhaps, it is a pearl.

4377.name: Boar's Tusk
4377.description: The tusk of a boar that looks somewhat similar to the ivory of an elephant.

4378.name: Sweet Potato
4378.description: A large sized sweet potato that was just plucked out of the soil. You s it or roast it. It will make a delicious treat.

4379.name: Beast's Claws
4379.description: White lion's sharp claws. It is rumored that it is being traded among collectors at a high price.

4380.name: Beast's Mane
4380.description: A white lion's luxuriant mane. It is rumored to be sold at a high price among collectors.

4381.name: Ginseng Root
4381.description: Rare medicine imported from the Orient.

4383.name: Bear's Gall
4383.description: The gall of a bear that is known to be highly effective in promoting one's health and well-being as well as having mysterious healing properties.

4384.name: Fresh Samon
4384.description: A fresh salmon that seems to have been just caught from a river.

4385.name: Sushi Riceball
4385.description: The Schuttgart type sushi rice ball. The delicious seasoning of well minced meat gets absorbed into the rice and produces a wonderful taste.

4386.name: Avellan Spice
4386.description: Exotic spice that has been imported from Avella of the Orient.

4387.name: Lucky Rabbit Weed
4387.description: Rabbit weed that is supposed to bring luck. It is the favorite food of rabbits and elpys.

4388.name: Malcom's Check
4388.description: A check of tremendous face value signed by Prince Malcom. It can be cashed at a warehouse in Town of Giran.

4389.name: Deposit Box Key
4389.description: A key for a private deposit box located in a warehouse in Town of Giran.

4390.name: Dwarven Royal Seal
4390.description: A royal seal made of carved jade. It is engraved with the seal of the Dwarven royal family.

4391.name: Dwarven Royal Crown
4391.description: A king's crown made of gold. It is engraved with the seal of the Dwarven royal family.

4392.name: Dwarven Dance Manual
4392.description: A dance manual that details ballroom dancing techniques. This book will make you a dancing hero!

4393.name: Calculator
4393.description: Allows one to perform a simple calculation.

4394.name: Hanellin's White Flower
4394.description: A mark of Hanellin. Along with your companions each carrying a red flower and yellow flower respectively, go to Town of Aden to see her.

4395.name: Hanellin's Red Flower
4395.description: A mark of Hanellin. Along with your companions each carrying a white flower and yellow flower respectively, go to Town of Aden to see her.

4396.name: Hanellin's Yellow Flower
4396.description: A mark of Hanellin. Along with your companions each carrying a white flower and red flower respectively, go to Town of Aden to see her.

4397.name: Book of Saint
4397.description: The book of Saint Solina. Take it along with the blood of a Saint and the bough of a Saint to Magister Hanellin.

4398.name: Blood of Saint
4398.description: The blood of Saint Solina, hardened into a dark-colored substance contained in a glass bottle. Take it, along with the Book of Saint and the Bough of Saint to Magister Hanellin.

4399.name: Bough of Saint
4399.description: The Scepter of Saint Solina. It appears to be just a dead dry tree branch. Take it along with the book of a Saint and the blood of a Saint and take it to Magister Hanellin.
